{
  "page": "Frey Pies/Theories",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table align=\"right\" width=\"180px\" style=\"float:right; margin: 0em 0em 1em 1em;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th style=\"text-align: center; background-color:#c2c2c2; font-size:12px; -moz-border-radius-topleft:10px;-moz-border-radius-topright:10px;\">&#160;Theories&#160;may&#160;be&#160;removed&#160;if&#160;...&#160;\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"font-size:11px; text-align: left; background-color:#eeeeee; font-weight:lighter;-moz-border-radius-bottomleft:10px;-moz-border-radius-bottomright:10px;padding-right: 1em; padding-left: .5em; padding-right: .5em;\">\n<ol><li>Stated as questions or possibilities.</li>\n<li>More appropriate for another article.</li>\n<li>Illogical or previously disproven.</li>\n<li>Proven by canon source, and moved to main page.</li>\n<li>Speculative and lacking any evidence to support arguments.</li>\n<li>Responding to another theory (use <a href=\"/index.php?title=Talk:Frey_Pies/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Talk:Frey Pies/Theories (page does not exist)\">discussion page</a> instead).</li></ol>\n<dl><dd><ul><li><small>This does not include responses that are also standalone theories.</small></li>\n<li><small>Usage of an indented bullet does not imply the statement is a response.</small></li></ul></dd></dl>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The <b>Frey Pies Theory</b> suggests that <a href=\"/index.php/Wyman_Manderly\" title=\"Wyman Manderly\">Wyman Manderly</a> orders the killing of three Freys (<a href=\"/index.php/Rhaegar_Frey\" title=\"Rhaegar Frey\">Rhaegar</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Symond_Frey\" title=\"Symond Frey\">Symond</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Jared_Frey\" title=\"Jared Frey\">Jared</a>) who disappear on the way from <a href=\"/index.php/White_Harbor\" title=\"White Harbor\">White Harbor</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Barrowton\" title=\"Barrowton\">Barrowton</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> According to the theory, Lord Manderly then has the men baked into the three huge pork pies he brings for the <a href=\"/index.php/Wedding_of_Ramsay_Bolton_and_Arya_Stark\" title=\"Wedding of Ramsay Bolton and Arya Stark\">wedding of Ramsay Bolton and Arya Stark</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">Winterfell</a>. The pies are described as <i>\"three great wedding pies, as wide across as wagon wheels, their flaky crusts stuffed to bursting with carrots, onions, turnips, parsnips, mushrooms, and chunks of seasoned pork swimming in a savory brown gravy.\"</i><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Supporting_Evidence\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Supporting Evidence</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Behind_the_scenes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Behind the scenes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Supporting_Evidence\">Supporting Evidence</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Frey_Pies/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Supporting Evidence\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Wyman_Manderly\" title=\"Wyman Manderly\">Wyman Manderly</a> tells <a href=\"/index.php/Davos_Seaworth\" title=\"Davos Seaworth\">Davos Seaworth</a> that he does not believe the lies the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Frey\" title=\"House Frey\">Freys</a> have been saying about the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Wedding\" title=\"Red Wedding\">Red Wedding</a>, and he knows his son <a href=\"/index.php/Wendel_Manderly\" title=\"Wendel Manderly\">Wendel</a> was murdered by them in violation of <a href=\"/index.php/Guest_right\" title=\"Guest right\">guest right</a>. He says that he had to appease the three Freys at <a href=\"/index.php/White_Harbor\" title=\"White Harbor\">White Harbor</a> while his son <a href=\"/index.php/Wylis_Manderly\" title=\"Wylis Manderly\">Wylis</a> was held <a href=\"/index.php/Hostage\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hostage\">hostage</a> by the <a href=\"/index.php/Lannisters\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lannisters\">Lannisters</a>, but now his son is home.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Wyman tells Davos he must travel to <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">Winterfell</a> for a <a href=\"/index.php/Wedding_of_Ramsay_Bolton_and_Arya_Stark\" title=\"Wedding of Ramsay Bolton and Arya Stark\">wedding</a>, along with the Freys. Wyman plans to give the three Freys <a href=\"/index.php/Guest_right\" title=\"Guest right\">guest gifts</a>, a tradition that marks a guest's departure and the end of the obligations of a host to follow guest right.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Rhaegar, Symond, and Jared Frey, riding on the fine <a href=\"/index.php/Horse\" title=\"Horse\">horses</a> that Wyman has gifted them, disappear while on the road from White Harbor to <a href=\"/index.php/Barrowton\" title=\"Barrowton\">Barrowton</a>. According to <a href=\"/index.php/Roose_Bolton\" title=\"Roose Bolton\">Roose Bolton</a>, Wyman insists the Freys traveled ahead of his column out of impatience over Wyman's slow pace, and he is distraught at their disappearance.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Ramsay_Bolton\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ramsay Bolton\">Ramsay Bolton</a> searches for them, along with his <a href=\"/index.php/Squire\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Squire\">squires</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Walder_Frey_(son_of_Jammos)\" title=\"Walder Frey (son of Jammos)\">Big Walder</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Walder_Frey_(son_of_Merrett)\" title=\"Walder Frey (son of Merrett)\">Little Walder Frey</a>, but they cannot be found. Big Walder tells <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a> he never expected to find his cousins. He believes that Wyman had them killed, saying that's what he would do if he were Wyman.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> <div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:452px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Jake_Murray_manderlys_scheme.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/ad/Jake_Murray_manderlys_scheme.jpg/450px-Jake_Murray_manderlys_scheme.jpg\" width=\"450\" height=\"238\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/ad/Jake_Murray_manderlys_scheme.jpg/675px-Jake_Murray_manderlys_scheme.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/a/ad/Jake_Murray_manderlys_scheme.jpg/900px-Jake_Murray_manderlys_scheme.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Jake_Murray_manderlys_scheme.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Wyman_Manderly\" title=\"Wyman Manderly\">Wyman Manderly</a> and his three pies, by Jake Murray © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div></li>\n<li>Lord Wyman presents three huge pork pies at the wedding in <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">Winterfell</a>, three matching the three missing Freys. Wyman serves portions to Roose, <a href=\"/index.php/Walda_Frey\" title=\"Walda Frey\">Walda Bolton</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Hosteen_Frey\" title=\"Hosteen Frey\">Hosteen Frey</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Aenys_Frey\" title=\"Aenys Frey\">Aenys Frey</a>, urging them to eat and praising the flavor. He serves them with great (drunken) exuberance. Wyman himself eats two portions from each pie.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>As he leaves the wedding feast, Lord Wyman drunkenly tells the bard <a href=\"/index.php/Mance_Rayder\" title=\"Mance Rayder\">Abel</a> to sing about the <a href=\"/index.php/Rat_Cook\" title=\"Rat Cook\">Rat Cook</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> a legendary <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a> cook who killed an <a href=\"/index.php/Andal\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Andal\">Andal</a> king's son and baked him into a pie he then <a href=\"/index.php/Cannibalism\" title=\"Cannibalism\">served to his father</a>. (Shortly after <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran Stark</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Dream\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dream\">dreamed</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Robb_Stark\" title=\"Robb Stark\">Robb Stark</a>'s death at the Red Wedding, he reflected on the legend of the Rat Cook: he was transformed into a giant white rat by the <a href=\"/index.php/Gods\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gods\">gods</a>, not because of his deeds, but specifically because he dishonored guest right.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>) A song about that subject would typically be considered too gruesome for a wedding.</li>\n<li>Hosteen and Aenys Frey later confront Lord Wyman about their missing relatives. In their argument, Hosteen says he will serve Wyman \"all the bloody bits you can stomach\", and Wyman laughs.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Frey_Pies/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>My son <a href=\"/index.php/Wendel_Manderly\" title=\"Wendel Manderly\">Wendel</a> came to the <a href=\"/index.php/Twins\" title=\"Twins\">Twins</a> a guest. He ate Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Walder_Frey\" title=\"Walder Frey\">Walder</a>'s <a href=\"/index.php/Guest_right\" title=\"Guest right\">bread and salt</a>, and hung his <a href=\"/index.php/Sword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sword\">sword</a> upon the wall to feast with friends. And they murdered him. <b><a href=\"/index.php/Red_Wedding\" title=\"Red Wedding\">Murdered</a></b>, I say, and may <a href=\"/index.php/House_Frey\" title=\"House Frey\">the Freys</a> choke upon their fables. I drink with <a href=\"/index.php/Jared_Frey\" title=\"Jared Frey\">Jared</a>, jape with <a href=\"/index.php/Symond_Frey\" title=\"Symond Frey\">Symond</a>, promise <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaegar_Frey\" title=\"Rhaegar Frey\">Rhaegar</a> the hand of <a href=\"/index.php/Wynafryd_Manderly\" title=\"Wynafryd Manderly\">my own beloved granddaughter</a> ... but never think that means I have forgotten. The <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">north</a> remembers, Lord Davos. The north remembers, and the <a href=\"/index.php/Mummer\" title=\"Mummer\">mummer</a>'s farce is almost done. <a href=\"/index.php/Wylis_Manderly\" title=\"Wylis Manderly\">My son</a> is home.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Wyman_Manderly\" title=\"Wyman Manderly\">Wyman Manderly</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Davos_Seaworth\" title=\"Davos Seaworth\">Davos Seaworth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Wyman:</b> The <a href=\"/index.php/House_Frey\" title=\"House Frey\">Freys</a> came here by sea. They have no <a href=\"/index.php/Horse\" title=\"Horse\">horses</a> with them, so I shall present each of them with a palfrey as a <a href=\"/index.php/Guest_right\" title=\"Guest right\">guest gift</a>. Do hosts still give guest gifts in the south?<br />\n</p><p><b>Davos:</b> Some do, my lord. On the day their guest departs.<br />\n</p>\n<b>Wyman:</b> Perhaps you understand, then.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Wyman_Manderly\" title=\"Wyman Manderly\">Wyman Manderly</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Davos_Seaworth\" title=\"Davos Seaworth\">Davos Seaworth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Theon:</b> Did you find your cousins, my lord?<br />\n<b>Walder:</b> No. I never thought we would. They're dead. Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Wyman_Manderly\" title=\"Wyman Manderly\">Wyman</a> had them killed. That's what I would have done if I was him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Walder_Frey_(son_of_Jammos)\" title=\"Walder Frey (son of Jammos)\">Big Walder Frey</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Wedding_pies_by_Jaydeewis.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/a2/Wedding_pies_by_Jaydeewis.png/350px-Wedding_pies_by_Jaydeewis.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"175\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/a2/Wedding_pies_by_Jaydeewis.png/525px-Wedding_pies_by_Jaydeewis.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/a/a2/Wedding_pies_by_Jaydeewis.png/700px-Wedding_pies_by_Jaydeewis.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Wedding_pies_by_Jaydeewis.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The three wedding pies, by Jaydeewis ©</div></div></div>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The best pie you have ever tasted, my lords. Wash it down with <a href=\"/index.php/Arbor_gold\" title=\"Arbor gold\">Arbor gold</a> and savor every bite. I know I shall.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Wyman_Manderly\" title=\"Wyman Manderly\">Wyman Manderly</a>, during the <a href=\"/index.php/Wedding_of_Ramsay_Bolton_and_Arya_Stark\" title=\"Wedding of Ramsay Bolton and Arya Stark\">wedding feast</a> of \"<a href=\"/index.php/Jeyne_Poole\" title=\"Jeyne Poole\">Arya Stark</a>\" and <a href=\"/index.php/Ramsay_Snow\" title=\"Ramsay Snow\">Ramsay Bolton</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>No taste for pork pie, my lord? The best pork pie we ever tasted, <a href=\"/index.php/Wyman_Manderly\" title=\"Wyman Manderly\">our fat friend</a> would have us believe. Have you ever seen a fat man so happy? He is almost dancing. Serving with his own hands.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Barbrey_Dustin\" title=\"Barbrey Dustin\">Barbrey Dustin</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Hosteen:</b> Where are my kin, Manderly? Tell me that. Your guests, who brought <a href=\"/index.php/Wendel_Manderly\" title=\"Wendel Manderly\">your son</a> back to you.\"\n</p><p><b>Wyman:</b> His bones, you mean. I recall them well. <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaegar_Frey\" title=\"Rhaegar Frey\">Rhaegar</a> of the round shoulders, with his glib tongue. Bold Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jared_Frey\" title=\"Jared Frey\">Jared</a>, so swift to draw his steel. <a href=\"/index.php/Symond_Frey\" title=\"Symond Frey\">Symond</a> the <a href=\"/index.php/Spymaster\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Spymaster\">spymaster</a>, always clinking <a href=\"/index.php/Coin\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Coin\">coins</a>. They brought home Wendel's bones. It was <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a> who returned <a href=\"/index.php/Wylis_Manderly\" title=\"Wylis Manderly\">Wylis</a> to me, safe and whole, as he had promised. A man of his word, Lord Tywin, <a href=\"/index.php/The_Seven\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The Seven\">Seven</a> save his soul. The road has many dangers, ser. I gave your brothers <a href=\"/index.php/Guest_right\" title=\"Guest right\">guest gifts</a> when we took our leave of <a href=\"/index.php/White_Harbor\" title=\"White Harbor\">White Harbor</a>. We swore we would meet again at the <a href=\"/index.php/Wedding_of_Ramsay_Bolton_and_Arya_Stark\" title=\"Wedding of Ramsay Bolton and Arya Stark\">wedding</a>. Many and more bore witness to our parting.<br />\n<b>Aenys:</b> Many and more? Or you and yours?<br />\n<b>Wyman:</b> What are you suggesting, Frey? I do not like your tone, ser. No, not one bloody bit.<br />\n</p>\n<b>Hosteen:</b> Step out into the yard, you sack of suet, and I'll serve you all the bloody bits that you can stomach.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Hosteen_Frey\" title=\"Hosteen Frey\">Hosteen Frey</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Wyman_Manderly\" title=\"Wyman Manderly\">Wyman Manderly</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Aenys_Frey\" title=\"Aenys Frey\">Aenys Frey</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Behind_the_scenes\">Behind the scenes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Frey_Pies/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Behind the scenes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Human flesh reportedly tastes much like pork;<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> see also the term \"<a href=\"http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/long_pig\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"wikt:long pig\">long pig</a>\".</li>\n<li>See also <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_Shakespeare\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:William Shakespeare\">William Shakespeare</a>'s <i><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Titus_Andronicus#Synopsis\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Titus Andronicus\">Titus Andronicus</a></i>, where a man avenges his family by serving someone their relatives baked into a pie.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Frey_Pies/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_32\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 32\">Chapter 32</a>, Reek III.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\">2.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\">2.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\">2.4</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_37\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 37\">Chapter 37</a>, The Prince of Winterfell.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">3.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\">3.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\">3.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-3\">3.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_29\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 29\">Chapter 29</a>, Davos IV.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_56\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 56\">Chapter 56</a>, Bran IV.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\">5.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\">5.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_46\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 46\">Chapter 46</a>, A Ghost in Winterfell.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Smithsonian Magazine: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/human-flesh-looks-beef-taste-more-elusive-180949562/\">Human Flesh Looks Like Beef, But the Taste Is More Elusive</a> (February 3, 2014)</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403160019\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.051 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.053 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 1601/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 9374/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 11541/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 3976/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 9/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 5826/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   32.778      1 -total\n 78.0